dipping crutch
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number: 1
Definition:a long pole with an S-shaped hook on the end, used to push under sheep's heads in a swim, pot, or plunge dip.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain:Rural
Region:[none]
See:crutch, dipping pole
